      "SummaryText": "cies and the public, as well as post-incident decontamination of affected areas.  Our plan has been coordinated and verified with the St. Clair County Local Emergency Planning Committee (LEPC).\n\nSolvay Fluorides, LLC. Alorton has an onsite Emergency Response Team, trained to respond to onsite emergencies beyond initiating emergency response from outside agencies.  The ERG team conducts quarterly drills and coordinates with both the local fire departments and LEPC.\n\nTo ensure proper functioning, our emergency response equipment is regularly inspected and serviced.  In addition, the plan is promptly updated to reflect any pertinent changes taking place within our processes that would require a modified emergency response.\n\n7.\tPlanned Changes to Improve Safety\nSafety improvement is an ongoing process at this facility.  Periodic inspections and evaluations are performed to assess the safe practices of maintenance and operations.\n\nThis facility resolves recommendations from PHA\u00c2\u00bfs and incident investigations, some of which may result in modifications to plant design and operating procedures."
